      "description": "The [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} moves up to its Speed without provoking Opportunity Attacks. The [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} can move through the spaces of Large or smaller creatures if it has room inside itself to contain them (see the mmOozeCube000000 trait).\n\nDexterity Saving Throw: DC [[lookup @save.dc.value activity=5o0Bh8PQaojx5XMx]], each creature whose space the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} enters for the first time during this move.\n\nFailure: [[/damage average]] damage, and the target is engulfed. An engulfed target is &amp;Reference[suffocating], can't cast spells with a Verbal component, has the &amp;Reference[Restrained apply=false] condition, and takes [[/damage average]] damage at the start of each of the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster}'s turns. When the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} moves, the engulfed target moves with it. An engulfed target can try to escape by taking an action to make a [[/check ability=str skill=ath dc=@abilities.str.dc]] check. On a successful check, the target escapes and enters the nearest unoccupied space.\n\nSuccess: Half damage, and the target moves to an unoccupied space within 5 feet of the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster}'s. If there is no unoccupied space, the target fails the save instead.",
