      "description": "The [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} fills its entire space and is transparent. Other creatures can enter that space, but a creature that does so is subjected to the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster}'s Engulf and has Disadvantage on the saving throw.\n\nCreatures inside the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} have &amp;Reference[Total Cover], and the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} can hold one Large creature or up to four Medium or Small creatures inside itself at a time.\n\nAs an action, a creature within [[lookup @range.value activity=EcTOfXWsDJRHLydy]] [[lookup @range.units activity=EcTOfXWsDJRHLydy]]. of the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} can pull a creature or an object out of the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} by succeeding on a [[/check dc=12 ability=str skill=ath format=long]], and the puller takes [[/damage average activity=PMCvyqxfUYiPzNK8]] damage.",
